  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective is to investigate neuro-anatomical correlates of the regulation of energy
      intake by means of functional MRI. Administration of glucose as well as fructose is followed
      by functional brain MRI, and findings are correlated with serum glucagon-like peptide 1
      (GLP-1) levels as an endogenous satiety signal in obese humans.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
